114.8	Arthur_Koestler	Arthur Koestler	Arthur Koestler CBE (5 September 1905, Budapest â€“ 3 March 1983, London) was a Hungarian-British author and journalist. Koestler was born in Budapest and, apart from his early school years, was educated in Austria. In 1931 Koestler joined the Communist Party of Germany but, disillusioned by Stalinist atrocities, he resigned in 1938. In 1940 he published his novel Darkness at Noon, an anti-totalitarian work, which gained him international fame.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Arthur_Koestler.jpg/150px-Arthur_Koestler.jpg
